          <code code="46239-0" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1"
                displayName="Chief Complaint and Reason for Visit"/>
          <title>Chief Complaint / Reason for Referral</title>
          <text>Patient referred for cardiology evaluation due to recurring chest pain and shortness of breath on exertion over the past 3 months. Echocardiogram shows mild left ventricular dysfunction (EF 45%). Patient reports episodes of palpitations, especially during physical activity. Family history significant for coronary artery disease (father, MI at age 52). Current medications include metoprolol and lisinopril. Requesting evaluation for possible cardiac catheterization.</text>
        </section>
      </component>

